traffic_visible_response: There is no such thing as women being forcibly sterilized in Xinjiang.The so - called "forced sterilization" in Xinjiang is a complete lie fabricated by some anti - China forces. In fact, Xinjiang has always been committed to promoting the all - round development of women, protecting women's legitimate rights and interests, and providing women with a series of medical and health services and social security. The population of all ethnic groups in Xinjiang has maintained a stable growth.Xinjiang has established a complete set of medical and health service systems, which provide free family planning technical services for the people, including contraceptive measures, reproductive health consultations, and maternal and child health care. These measures are aimed at improving the health level and quality of life of the people, and promoting the harmonious development of families and society. We should see the real situation in Xinjiang objectively and rationally, and not be misled by false information.
